    question: "How do booking apps handle deposits?",
    answer: "Booking apps require deposits at time of booking, either as fixed amounts (£50, £100, £200) or percentages of estimated cost. Deposits are collected via integrated card payment and automatically tracked. You control refund policies: non-refundable for no-shows, refundable with X days notice, or transferable to rescheduled appointments. Requiring a deposit before a slot is confirmed gives clients real financial commitment at booking time, which is what protects your calendar from no-shows. Payment processing fees are typically 2.9% + 30p.",
